Six inmates remanded in Afaraukwu Correctional Facility in Umuahia North Local Government Area of Abia State have regained their freedom. The inmates, whose names were not immediately ascertained, were reportedly remanded in the facility in Umuahia, the state capital, over their inability to pay fines for various offences that they were asked to pay by various courts in the state. Our correspondent reports that the six inmates regained their freedom after the wife of the Speaker of Abia State House of Assembly Dr Mrs Onyinyechi Orji offset their various fines.   Bandits release two more Baptist students     Bandits kill 7, abduct 18 in attacks on Kaduna villages     NIMET alerts airline operators to poor visibility in eightâ€¦   While commending officers and men of the Nigeria Correctional Centre for their efforts in helping to reform the inmates Dr Mrs Orji said even though the inmates were paying for their infractions on society, stressed that they still have the opportunity of becoming better citizens. Mrs Orji also handed out some sums of money for their transportation to their various homes. - Advertisement - The freed inmates who were elated by the gesture of their benefactor prayed for her and her family.